WEBVTT

00:03.873 --> 00:08.225
♪♪

00:08.225 --> 00:10.749
This chart represents
the typical asset allocation

00:10.749 --> 00:12.316
of a high net worth individual.

00:12.316 --> 00:14.144
60% in equities,

00:14.144 --> 00:16.146
25% in municipal securities,

00:16.146 --> 00:18.844
10% in real estate,
and 5% in corporate bonds.

00:18.844 --> 00:21.499
It's balanced.
It's diversified.

00:21.499 --> 00:24.372
A conservative approach
that can sustain fluctuations

00:24.372 --> 00:27.201
in the stock market,
home prices, or interest rates.

00:27.201 --> 00:30.465
And this is
Normandy Parker's chart.

00:30.465 --> 00:34.556
90% of his assets
are tied down in one investment.

00:34.556 --> 00:36.123
Sourdough Subs.

00:36.123 --> 00:38.168
I mean, the only people
with less diversification

00:38.168 --> 00:39.735
in their portfolios
are drug dealers

00:39.735 --> 00:41.998
who stash their cash
underneath a mattress.

00:41.998 --> 00:44.479
All right, sir, we got
two homicide cases.

00:44.479 --> 00:46.220
Is math class really necessary?

00:46.220 --> 00:48.483
Keep going.

00:48.483 --> 00:50.833
Six months before
Normandy's shot,

00:50.833 --> 00:53.227
someone was building
a large short position

00:53.227 --> 00:54.880
in Sourdough Subs.

00:54.880 --> 00:57.361
What's a short position?Uh, it's when you place a bet

00:57.361 --> 01:00.364
that a company's stock
will go down instead of up.

01:00.364 --> 01:01.887
Normandy gets shot,

01:01.887 --> 01:04.716
and the stock drops 20%
in a straight line.

01:04.716 --> 01:06.327
So somebody made a fortune.

01:06.327 --> 01:08.285
So you short the stock,
you take Normandy out,

01:08.285 --> 01:10.853
and you, uh, get the cash
before anyone notices.

01:10.853 --> 01:13.638
I mean, it's a --
it's a smart idea.Yeah.

01:13.638 --> 01:16.119
Could Sam have been shorting
his own stock?

01:16.119 --> 01:19.209
It's doubtful. Sam was
the majority shareholder.

01:19.209 --> 01:21.472
He'd make $10 million
in the short position

01:21.472 --> 01:23.518
and lose $20 million
in stock value.

01:23.518 --> 01:28.088
I say if anything, Sam was
a victim of the short position.

01:28.088 --> 01:29.698
[ Muffled shouting ]

01:29.698 --> 01:31.526
If you're dissatisfied with
your Sourdough Sam sub,

01:31.526 --> 01:33.093
feel free to fill out
a comment card,

01:33.093 --> 01:35.356
and a customer representative
will get back to you

01:35.356 --> 01:37.836
as soon as possible.[ Spits ]

01:37.836 --> 01:40.230
[ Coughs,
speaks indistinctly ]

01:40.230 --> 01:41.927
[ Laughs ] Look...

01:41.927 --> 01:44.930
Yeah.
I'll get you your money.

01:44.930 --> 01:46.889
I just need more time.

01:46.889 --> 01:49.021
"I just need more time.
More time."

01:49.021 --> 01:50.632
They always need more time.

01:50.632 --> 01:54.375
I'll double your percentage.
20%.

01:55.941 --> 01:59.162
Yeah? [ Breathing heavily ]

01:59.162 --> 02:00.729
What?

02:04.689 --> 02:07.692
Oh. No, no more.

02:07.692 --> 02:09.651
Please. Oh!

02:09.651 --> 02:14.612
[ Sputtering ]

02:14.612 --> 02:16.048
More.[ Muffled shout ]

02:16.048 --> 02:18.529
[ Continues sputtering ]

02:18.529 --> 02:21.228
[ Muffled grunts ]

02:21.228 --> 02:23.491
Now.
[ Spits ]

02:23.491 --> 02:26.842
[ Coughs ]

02:26.842 --> 02:30.324
You never learn, Sam.[ Wheezing ]

02:30.324 --> 02:35.285
[ Gags, coughs ]

02:35.285 --> 02:38.114
[ Gasps ]

02:38.114 --> 02:40.508
[ Glass shatters ]Oh!

02:40.508 --> 02:42.466
[ Gasps ]

02:42.466 --> 02:45.295
No!

02:45.295 --> 02:47.993
Ah!

02:47.993 --> 02:52.389
Chow. Look, just think --
this thing through.

02:52.389 --> 02:54.217
I'm no good to you dead.

02:55.523 --> 02:58.090
Oh.

02:58.090 --> 03:00.136
Oh, please.

03:00.136 --> 03:04.793
[ Panting ]

03:04.793 --> 03:06.882
[ Shard clatters ]

03:08.579 --> 03:11.103
You have 48 hours
to get me my money.

03:11.103 --> 03:13.976
Or else next time,

03:13.976 --> 03:16.370
it won't be shitty sandwiches
down your mouth.

03:17.893 --> 03:20.635
Are we clear?
[ Exhaling ]

03:20.635 --> 03:22.854
Yeah?
Yeah.

03:24.726 --> 03:28.469
♪♪

03:39.523 --> 03:44.006
[ Woman shouting indistinctly ] Get out of my --

03:44.006 --> 03:45.355
[ Thud ] [ Screams ]

03:45.355 --> 03:49.968
[ Both breathing heavily ]

03:53.015 --> 03:55.539
She just jumped
in front of my car.

03:55.539 --> 03:56.975
You know, it could've happened
to anyone.

03:56.975 --> 03:58.542
Yeah, anyone who was drunk.

03:58.542 --> 04:00.849
Which is what the prosecution
will present.

04:00.849 --> 04:02.503
And then it's your job
to poke holes

04:02.503 --> 04:04.156
in their bullshit argument.

04:04.156 --> 04:05.984
Well, I can't do that
if you won't be honest with me.

04:05.984 --> 04:08.422
I have been honest.Why did Cassie move out?

04:08.422 --> 04:10.119
That's none
of your business.

04:10.119 --> 04:13.078
Okay, you have been withholding
information from me

04:13.078 --> 04:14.732
that is relevant to the case,

04:14.732 --> 04:16.908
and I can't
properly defend someone

04:16.908 --> 04:19.259
with my hands tied behind
my back.

04:20.956 --> 04:24.655
Cassie and I thought it would be
best to live separately

04:24.655 --> 04:27.354
after the accident,
for Michael's sake.

04:27.354 --> 04:28.920
Bullshit.

04:28.920 --> 04:30.400
Nobody moves out of her house
because her husband

04:30.400 --> 04:32.620
got into an accident.We had an argument.

04:32.620 --> 04:35.318
Okay? You happy?

04:37.102 --> 04:39.191
Cassie was all over me.

04:39.191 --> 04:42.194
What about?Oh, just...

04:42.194 --> 04:45.241
Picking and prodding and...

04:45.241 --> 04:48.157
Come on, just tell me
what happened.

04:50.507 --> 04:52.074
[ Indistinct conversation ]

04:52.074 --> 04:53.815
She thought
I was cheating on her.

04:53.815 --> 04:57.035
Okay, when, uh,
were you planning

04:57.035 --> 05:00.038
on telling me
that she can crucify us?

05:00.038 --> 05:01.562
She's not gonna go
against me.

05:01.562 --> 05:04.129
Oh, the scorned wife who can
put the final nail

05:04.129 --> 05:06.784
in the cross
of her cheating husband

05:06.784 --> 05:09.265
opts to testify
on his behalf?

05:10.571 --> 05:12.529
You need to fix this!I've tried.

05:12.529 --> 05:13.922
Try harder!

05:18.405 --> 05:21.408
♪♪

05:22.974 --> 05:25.020
Hi.

05:25.020 --> 05:26.630
Hey, Justin.Um...

05:26.630 --> 05:28.371
What brings you up here
with the living?

05:28.371 --> 05:30.330
Well, I have Normandy's
completed autopsy file

05:30.330 --> 05:31.853
and tox report,

05:31.853 --> 05:33.289
and there was nothing illegal
in his system

05:33.289 --> 05:36.292
at the time of his death.

05:36.292 --> 05:37.902
Cool. Thanks.

05:41.297 --> 05:42.994
[ Clears throat ]Is there something else?

05:42.994 --> 05:46.171
Yeah, um...

05:46.171 --> 05:48.391
Dinner. Tomorrow? Us?

05:50.175 --> 05:52.264
Me and you?

05:52.264 --> 05:55.355
But, I mean,
we work together, so...

05:55.355 --> 05:58.575
That's where most people meet,
statistically speaking, so...

05:58.575 --> 06:01.622
Yeah, it's -- it's different
for cops, right?

06:01.622 --> 06:04.102
Well, lucky for us,
I'm a doctor. I'm not a cop.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.278
So 8:00?

06:06.278 --> 06:08.063
And I'm used to women
being silent.

06:08.063 --> 06:10.195
They're usually lying
on a cold slab,

06:10.195 --> 06:12.241
waiting for me
to cut them up, but...

06:12.241 --> 06:14.504
[ Laughs ]
Uh, um...

06:14.504 --> 06:16.506
What's so funny?
What's up, Burn?

06:16.506 --> 06:18.465
Um...Um...

06:18.465 --> 06:19.901
Uh, I have to get back
downstairs.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.033
The, uh, dead are waiting.Yeah.

06:22.033 --> 06:25.167
All right. See you later.Bye.

06:25.167 --> 06:26.734
What did Burn want?

06:26.734 --> 06:30.215
Nothing, just --Koto: Hey, heads up.

06:30.215 --> 06:32.696
My office.

06:32.696 --> 06:35.525
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:35.525 --> 06:37.745
We matched on the bike used
in the Billy James murder.

06:37.745 --> 06:40.965
Where?Abandoned in Crissy Field.

06:40.965 --> 06:43.533
Same make and model from the
tire tracks found at the scene.

06:43.533 --> 06:44.795
Any prints?I doubt it.

06:44.795 --> 06:46.275
The bike was dumped
in a lake.

06:46.275 --> 06:48.712
But I sent it to the lab
for results just in case.

06:48.712 --> 06:50.845
Identifiable marks on the bike?

06:50.845 --> 06:53.891
It's a rental from
this bike shack in Crissy Field.

06:53.891 --> 06:56.024
On our way.

06:56.024 --> 06:57.504
Adler dug out the name

06:57.504 --> 06:59.897
of the broker who shorted
Sourdough Sub stock.

06:59.897 --> 07:01.421
Any connection to Normandy?

07:01.421 --> 07:03.988
Not that she could find.
Go prove her wrong.

07:03.988 --> 07:06.426
Got it.
Yeah.

07:06.426 --> 07:10.560
Listen, I want you to sell
50,000 shares at 32 1/2. Okay?

07:10.560 --> 07:13.955
32 1/2. And don't screw it
up this time!

07:15.522 --> 07:17.828
[ Receiver thuds ]There we go. Thank you.

07:19.221 --> 07:20.788
Well, don't just stand there
with your dick in your hand.

07:20.788 --> 07:22.659
We need to take
a look at your books.

07:22.659 --> 07:24.792
Oh, okay. You got a warrant
for that, sweetie?

07:24.792 --> 07:27.098
Her name is
Inspector Mulligan.

07:27.098 --> 07:29.274
Don't I know you?

07:29.274 --> 07:30.580
You don't.

07:30.580 --> 07:32.103
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:32.103 --> 07:34.236
You're that cop who shot
that unarmed black guy.

07:34.236 --> 07:37.369
Yeah. What's that like,
to shoot someone?

07:37.369 --> 07:40.547
You having fun?A little.

07:40.547 --> 07:43.898
Great. Let's have some fun.Ooh, yeah, there's a back room.

07:43.898 --> 07:45.595
It's very private if you want
to have your world rocked.

07:45.595 --> 07:47.162
What did you just say?

07:47.162 --> 07:48.990
I was thinking more along
the lines of discussing

07:48.990 --> 07:50.905
your involvement with...
[ Loudly ] insider trading.

07:50.905 --> 07:52.559
[ Clears throat ]

07:52.559 --> 07:55.257
Oh, I'm sorry.
Did I hit a nerve?

07:55.257 --> 07:59.304
[ Loudly ] I have never been
involved with insider trading.

07:59.304 --> 08:02.743
You recently set up an account
with somebody

08:02.743 --> 08:04.048
a few months ago --I start accounts all the time --

08:04.048 --> 08:05.876
Let me finish.

08:05.876 --> 08:08.792
This one was short a large
amount of Sourdough Sub stocks.

08:08.792 --> 08:10.577
Sourdough Subs. Okay, yes.

08:10.577 --> 08:13.841
It's a good multiple,
top performer in its sector.

08:13.841 --> 08:15.190
Uh, you know,
until the golden goose

08:15.190 --> 08:16.452
took two in the dome.
[ Chuckles ]

08:16.452 --> 08:17.888
[ Clears throat ] I made a --

08:17.888 --> 08:19.194
I made a fortune for my client
with that.

08:19.194 --> 08:23.285
We need to know the name
on that account.

08:23.285 --> 08:24.852
[ Loudly ] Look, we can
make this official,

08:24.852 --> 08:26.157
drag you in for questioning.

08:26.157 --> 08:28.769
Okay, okay, okay.

08:28.769 --> 08:31.902
[ Typing ]

08:31.902 --> 08:33.251
[ Computer clicks ]

08:33.251 --> 08:35.253
There it is. Otto Brooks.
Okay?

08:35.253 --> 08:37.517
You two ever meet?No, we only spoke on the phone.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.780
I just know his address, where
to send his monthly statements.

08:39.780 --> 08:43.305
1310 Hickey Road.Where is that?

08:43.305 --> 08:45.046
[ Paper rips ]

08:45.046 --> 08:47.614
DeBell Golf Club.

08:52.053 --> 08:55.056
♪♪

09:04.021 --> 09:06.937
Can I help you?No.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.375
There you go.

09:10.375 --> 09:11.725
See what happens
when you finish your swing?

09:11.725 --> 09:13.335
Terry: Excuse us.

09:13.335 --> 09:15.598
Otto Brooks?

09:17.644 --> 09:19.689
Guess that depends on
who's asking.

09:19.689 --> 09:22.649
[ Sniffs, clears throat ]

09:28.263 --> 09:31.396
Since when is it a crime to get
lucky in the stock market?

09:31.396 --> 09:33.921
It's not,
but accessory to murder is.

09:33.921 --> 09:36.314
Normandy dies,
and your bank account rises.

09:36.314 --> 09:38.578
That's -- that's not
a good look, Otto.

09:38.578 --> 09:42.103
Profiting off the downfall
of others is the American dream.

09:42.103 --> 09:44.801
Don't hate the player.
Hate the game.

09:44.801 --> 09:46.107
[ Scoffs ] Oh.

09:46.107 --> 09:48.239
Two years as a ski instructor
in Vail,

09:48.239 --> 09:52.156
one summer as a tennis pro
in Miami.

09:52.156 --> 09:56.204
Not exactly the profile
for a savvy investor.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.509
Yeah, how does a guy like you

09:57.509 --> 09:59.599
get enough money to play
the stock market?

09:59.599 --> 10:02.253
Maybe some divorcée liked the
way I looked with my shirt off,

10:02.253 --> 10:03.951
and wrote me a big fat check.

10:03.951 --> 10:07.084
Are we done here? I got another
lesson in 10 minutes.

10:07.084 --> 10:08.782
[ Grunts ][ Objects clatter ]

10:08.782 --> 10:10.522
[ Grunts ] Get this guy off me!
Get him off me!

10:10.522 --> 10:12.568
How 'bout I drag your ass
out of here

10:12.568 --> 10:14.701
in front of all your little rich
friends, huh? How 'bout that?

10:14.701 --> 10:16.746
Aah! Okay, okay! Don't!
You're gonna break my arm.

10:16.746 --> 10:19.053
I know. I know I am.

10:19.053 --> 10:21.577
Okay, okay, okay.
Just let me go. Let me go.

10:21.577 --> 10:24.624
[ Breathing heavily ]

10:29.019 --> 10:30.499
About six months ago,

10:30.499 --> 10:33.894
I got a call
from my old college roommate.

10:33.894 --> 10:36.374
Keep talking.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.855
We hadn't spoke in years.

10:38.855 --> 10:40.291
He asked me if I wanted
to make some money.

10:40.291 --> 10:42.032
I said,
"Sure, what's the catch?"

10:42.032 --> 10:43.468
He said, "No catch.

10:43.468 --> 10:45.427
"Just keep your mouth shut,
do as I say,

10:45.427 --> 10:47.342
and I'll make you
a million dollars."

10:47.342 --> 10:49.213
So I did.

10:49.213 --> 10:51.607
What's his name?

10:51.607 --> 10:54.175
[ Continues breathing heavily ]
Nick.

10:54.175 --> 10:58.483
Rosenthal. Nick Rosenthal.

10:58.483 --> 11:00.747
Normandy's business manager.

11:02.923 --> 11:05.926
♪♪

11:05.926 --> 11:08.929
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:12.323 --> 11:14.717
Doesn't anyone have a job?

11:14.717 --> 11:18.939
They're all in tech.
Free spirits and long lunches.

11:21.942 --> 11:23.160
Hey, enjoy your ride, guys.Thanks.

11:23.160 --> 11:24.466
And take lots of pictures.

11:24.466 --> 11:26.642
It's a beautiful day
for memories.

11:26.642 --> 11:28.209
Bike ride for
the handsome couple?

11:30.690 --> 11:32.517
Oh. What a shame.

11:32.517 --> 11:34.215
Yeah, we need to ask you about
a bike that was stolen here

11:34.215 --> 11:36.783
three days ago.I told the officer
the other day,

11:36.783 --> 11:38.480
people steal bikes
all the time.

11:38.480 --> 11:40.177
I stopped reporting 'em
because no one ever gets caught.

11:40.177 --> 11:41.657
Here's the make
and model number.

11:41.657 --> 11:43.311
We need to find the name
of the person,

11:43.311 --> 11:44.878
whoever rented
that particular bike,

11:44.878 --> 11:46.836
of all the ones
that were stolen.

11:46.836 --> 11:48.708
Let me check the computer.Thanks.

11:56.759 --> 11:59.719
Devin and Sarah Steckler.

11:59.719 --> 12:02.025
Steckler. Got it.Thanks.

12:02.025 --> 12:03.505
You got it.

12:04.985 --> 12:07.683
Uh, so...

12:07.683 --> 12:09.685
you rented the bike
from the kiosk.

12:09.685 --> 12:11.469
And then...

12:11.469 --> 12:14.168
We went to this really cute
sidewalk café on Stanyan Street.

12:14.168 --> 12:17.649
They have the best crab benedict
I have ever tasted.

12:17.649 --> 12:19.521
They use too much hollandaise.

12:19.521 --> 12:21.218
They do not.

12:21.218 --> 12:22.524
If you could stick to
information about the bike,

12:22.524 --> 12:23.830
that would be very helpful.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.396
There was a bike rack outside,
so we --

12:25.396 --> 12:27.398
Locked our bikes and didn't
think much of it.

12:27.398 --> 12:29.357
I locked mine, but Sarah didn't.

12:29.357 --> 12:30.706
Yes, I did.

12:30.706 --> 12:32.664
Then how did it get stolen?

12:32.664 --> 12:35.189
I don't know, Devin.
Why don't you tell me?

12:35.189 --> 12:36.843
You seem
to know everything.

12:36.843 --> 12:38.409
Because you didn't lock
the bike.

12:38.409 --> 12:42.500
Do we really have to do this
in front of the police?

12:42.500 --> 12:44.938
I'm sure they've seen worse.

12:44.938 --> 12:47.375
Mm-hmm.We have.

12:47.375 --> 12:50.030
Mm.[ Whispers ] Okay.

12:50.030 --> 12:51.771
When we were done
with lunch,

12:51.771 --> 12:53.555
we came outside to finish
our ride around the park and --

12:53.555 --> 12:57.254
One -- one bike was gone.

12:57.254 --> 12:58.690
Do you remember the name
of the restaurant?

12:58.690 --> 13:01.650
Cafe Fruits De Mer.
And ask for Andre.

13:01.650 --> 13:03.521
Yeah, tell him Devin sent you.

13:03.521 --> 13:04.871
Or Sarah.

13:04.871 --> 13:06.960
He's a personal friend of ours.

13:09.049 --> 13:12.052
[ French accent ] Devin
and Sarah? Never heard of them.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.923
They said they were
personal friends.

13:13.923 --> 13:17.100
Well, it is my job to make
people feel special.

13:17.100 --> 13:18.928
And I am very good
at my job.
Huh.

13:18.928 --> 13:20.843
Look, we're just trying to track
down a bike that was stolen

13:20.843 --> 13:22.410
in front of your restaurant.

13:22.410 --> 13:25.761
If it's not on my premises,
then it is not my problem.

13:25.761 --> 13:27.894
Do you have security cameras?[ Chuckles ]

13:27.894 --> 13:29.417
We're not
some cheap mini-mart

13:29.417 --> 13:31.462
with a camera
hanging on the walls.

13:31.462 --> 13:32.855
Look, um, here's our card.

13:32.855 --> 13:34.074
You think of anything,
anything at all,

13:34.074 --> 13:35.640
give us a call, okay?

13:35.640 --> 13:39.731
Well, happy hour is 5 to 7.
You come back anytime.

13:39.731 --> 13:41.908
Ask for Andre.

13:41.908 --> 13:43.866
Merci.
Mm.

13:46.434 --> 13:47.783
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:47.783 --> 13:50.264
So you steal a bike
in broad daylight

13:50.264 --> 13:51.743
and use it as a getaway
for murder.

13:51.743 --> 13:53.136
I mean, it just doesn't
make sense.

13:53.136 --> 13:54.659
We need eyes.

13:54.659 --> 13:56.923
There's gotta be
a security camera somewhere

13:56.923 --> 13:58.359
that must've seen something.

14:00.013 --> 14:02.842
There. Right there.

14:02.842 --> 14:04.974
Bingo, baby.

14:04.974 --> 14:07.890
Keefer: That's your bike
on the left.

14:10.458 --> 14:12.329
Shit! We're blind.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.765
Um, fast forward.

14:13.765 --> 14:16.333
Fast forwarding isn't gonna make
a bus disappear.

14:16.333 --> 14:17.726
Please.

14:21.817 --> 14:23.340
Three bikes.Are you kidding me?

14:23.340 --> 14:25.995
He takes it exactly when
we can't see him?

14:25.995 --> 14:27.649
You think
he just got lucky?

14:27.649 --> 14:30.217
That bus runs every 30 minutes,
like clockwork.

14:30.217 --> 14:32.393
Hmm.

14:32.393 --> 14:34.221
He knew that bus was
gonna block us.

14:35.657 --> 14:37.528
[ Exhales slowly ]

14:37.528 --> 14:41.402
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:43.186 --> 14:44.884
Michael: So I told her,

14:44.884 --> 14:48.409
I'm like,
"You're a bad teacher."[ Horn honks ]

14:48.409 --> 14:49.714
She didn't believe me,
she's like...

14:49.714 --> 14:52.195
[ Horn honks ]

14:54.763 --> 14:57.635
Why do I need to take it...[ Horn blares ]

14:57.635 --> 14:59.202
I gotta go.Okay, bye.

14:59.202 --> 15:00.508
I'll see you. See you guys.All right.

15:00.508 --> 15:01.770
Bye.
Yeah.

15:04.729 --> 15:06.122
[ Door opens ]

15:06.122 --> 15:07.950
[ Clears throat ]

15:07.950 --> 15:10.910
Isn't make me go to my SAT prep
during my summer vacation

15:10.910 --> 15:12.607
enough punishment?

15:12.607 --> 15:14.957
You have to come and embarrass
me in front of my friends?

15:14.957 --> 15:16.916
Come on, Michael,
just get in the car.

15:21.224 --> 15:22.704
[ Door closes ]

15:26.186 --> 15:28.579
What do you want, Dad?

15:28.579 --> 15:30.059
I'm sorry.

15:33.280 --> 15:36.152
Did you hear me, Michael?

15:36.152 --> 15:38.241
Sorry for what?

15:38.241 --> 15:40.765
Ruining my last year
of high school?

15:40.765 --> 15:43.899
Leaving me
to take care of Mom?

15:46.989 --> 15:50.253
For all of it.

15:50.253 --> 15:52.473
Just -- I just need
my family back.

15:52.473 --> 15:56.390
Maybe we don't needyou.

15:56.390 --> 15:59.175
Just wait. Wait.

15:59.175 --> 16:02.265
Okay?

16:02.265 --> 16:04.311
All right.

16:04.311 --> 16:07.879
Let me tell it to you
straight.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.230
If your mother and I
get divorced,

16:10.230 --> 16:13.189
I'll have to support
two separate households.

16:13.189 --> 16:17.759
I can't do that andsend you
to college out of state.

16:17.759 --> 16:19.587
Okay. We are in this mess
because of you.

16:19.587 --> 16:21.719
Why do I have to suffer
your consequences?

16:21.719 --> 16:23.634
You don't.

16:23.634 --> 16:26.463
All you have to do is help me
get our family back together.

16:26.463 --> 16:27.943
You do that,

16:27.943 --> 16:31.164
and I'll pay for
whatever school you want.

16:31.164 --> 16:34.689
Otherwise, you're going
to community college

16:34.689 --> 16:36.604
right here in the Bay Area.

16:38.040 --> 16:40.956
It's always some sort
of deal with you.

16:42.914 --> 16:45.091
[ Car door opens ]This is ridiculous.

16:45.091 --> 16:46.701
[ Car door closes ]

16:54.622 --> 16:57.668
♪♪

17:00.367 --> 17:02.847
Explain this.

17:02.847 --> 17:06.808
Well, my reconstruction expert
was reviewing the tire tracks

17:06.808 --> 17:08.157
from the crime scene.

17:08.157 --> 17:10.551
1,000 bucks
to look at evidence?

17:10.551 --> 17:12.857
[ Chuckles ] If you want to put
a price tag on your freedom,

17:12.857 --> 17:15.251
you might want to start looking
for another lawyer.

17:17.297 --> 17:18.950
Is that a threat?

17:18.950 --> 17:21.257
All I'm saying is it is better
to be poor and free

17:21.257 --> 17:22.650
than rich and locked up.

17:22.650 --> 17:25.174
Huh. Yeah.

17:25.174 --> 17:26.828
What about this?

17:26.828 --> 17:28.525
We need to focus on your case,

17:28.525 --> 17:30.614
not squabble over
my hourly rate.

17:30.614 --> 17:34.488
Oh, don't you ever forget
who works for whom.

17:34.488 --> 17:37.360
Okay.
This isn't a courtroom,

17:37.360 --> 17:41.190
and you can't bully me like
you used to do with the jurors.

17:41.190 --> 17:45.760
I practiced law
with honor and integrity.

17:45.760 --> 17:51.157
I wasn't some two-bit DUI lawyer
chasing the next paycheck.

17:51.157 --> 17:54.899
Well, thistwo-bit DUI lawyer

17:54.899 --> 18:00.557
is the only thing between
you and prison bars.

18:00.557 --> 18:02.124
[ Indistinct conversations,
door squeaks ]

18:02.124 --> 18:03.821
Remember that.

18:03.821 --> 18:06.607
You're kicking me out?

18:06.607 --> 18:08.478
You're gonna
have to get used to the fact

18:08.478 --> 18:10.567
that you're not
in control anymore.

18:10.567 --> 18:13.092
Those days are over, Mario.

18:15.398 --> 18:17.661
[ Picks up briefcase ]

18:20.969 --> 18:22.579
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:22.579 --> 18:24.146
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]Psst!

18:30.935 --> 18:33.199
I heard was Mr. Arkin said.

18:33.199 --> 18:35.505
You don't have to live
like that.

18:38.595 --> 18:40.815
Manifest your destiny.

18:40.815 --> 18:43.122
Be the future
you want to be.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.645
And what do I do with this?

18:44.645 --> 18:46.908
Hang it in a place that you'll
look at every day.

18:46.908 --> 18:51.130
Let it be the guide
to getting back your power.

18:51.130 --> 18:52.566
It's half done.

18:52.566 --> 18:54.089
Oh, on purpose.

18:54.089 --> 18:57.440
You can finish it
with your wife. Together.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.494
Okay, we'll be here.

19:07.494 --> 19:09.235
All right.[ Receiver thuds ]

19:09.235 --> 19:11.193
Nick's on his way.

19:11.193 --> 19:14.196
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

19:15.545 --> 19:18.418
You need to get that?No.

19:24.859 --> 19:27.688
What?

19:27.688 --> 19:30.604
Come make coffee with me
for a second?

19:34.216 --> 19:36.523
Ah, what's up?

19:36.523 --> 19:39.221
Um...

19:39.221 --> 19:41.571
Burnside keeps
asking me out.

19:43.312 --> 19:44.705
Burnside?

19:44.705 --> 19:46.794
Yeah.

19:46.794 --> 19:48.883
What do you think
I should do?

19:48.883 --> 19:51.799
Burnside.

19:51.799 --> 19:55.281
I...I didn't think
he had it in him.

19:55.281 --> 19:57.979
Well, he clearly does.

19:57.979 --> 20:00.547
Well... [ Chuckles ]

20:00.547 --> 20:02.549
Go ahead, Burnside.

20:02.549 --> 20:05.204
So...what should I do?

20:05.204 --> 20:07.162
What -- look here, I'm not
gonna be your Dear Abby.

20:07.162 --> 20:08.990
No, no, no. I'm not --
I'm not asking you to be.

20:08.990 --> 20:11.558
I'm just...you know.

20:14.300 --> 20:18.173
I think, um,
I think Burnside's cool.

20:18.173 --> 20:19.696
You know, he's a nice guy.

20:19.696 --> 20:21.916
And I think if you want
to go out with him,

20:21.916 --> 20:23.265
you should go out with him.

20:25.789 --> 20:27.313
You know?

20:27.313 --> 20:29.445
Okay, well, I'm only saying it
because, you know,

20:29.445 --> 20:31.491
I'm trying to be an adult
and move on from...

20:31.491 --> 20:36.496
what happened between us
in a responsible way.Oh, yeah. I get it.

20:36.496 --> 20:39.281
That's the only reason
I've even thinking about it.Yeah.

20:39.281 --> 20:42.502
Well, there's your answer
right there. Have a good date.

20:45.809 --> 20:48.421
[ Footsteps depart,
door opens ]

20:48.421 --> 20:50.988
Hey.

20:50.988 --> 20:52.468
Can I help you?

20:52.468 --> 20:53.948
Yeah, this one said
she had information

20:53.948 --> 20:55.341
on Siletti's accident.

20:56.951 --> 21:00.302
Molk: You're looking
at felony drug possession.

21:00.302 --> 21:03.479
Navarro: It's not like you got
pinched with a gram of weed.

21:03.479 --> 21:04.915
Heroin ain't no joke.

21:04.915 --> 21:08.267
Molk:
Think about your future.I am.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.791
That's why I'm not talking
to no cops for nothing.

21:10.791 --> 21:12.183
We can't promise anything

21:12.183 --> 21:13.576
because it's out
of our jurisdiction --

21:13.576 --> 21:15.448
I don't care about that.

21:15.448 --> 21:19.016
Just let me go home, and I'll
tell you what you wanna know.

21:19.016 --> 21:21.280
I will personally walk this
into the A.G.'s office

21:21.280 --> 21:23.151
and tell them how
cooperative you've been.

21:23.151 --> 21:26.720
A.G.? What's an A.G.?

21:26.720 --> 21:29.418
This case is being handled by

21:29.418 --> 21:32.900
the Attorney General's office,
not the SFPD.

21:32.900 --> 21:35.555
So?
What does that mean for me?

21:35.555 --> 21:39.385
What that means is that you tell
us everything you know,

21:39.385 --> 21:41.822
and we will do our best
to make sure

21:41.822 --> 21:43.432
your charges are dropped.

21:46.870 --> 21:48.742
You promise?

21:48.742 --> 21:51.527
My word.

21:54.791 --> 21:56.271
Fine.

21:56.271 --> 21:58.012
What do you wanna know?

21:58.012 --> 22:00.754
Tell us what you saw.I saw it all.

22:00.754 --> 22:04.410
The car hit the woman,
the body flying through the air.

22:04.410 --> 22:05.889
Where were you?

22:05.889 --> 22:07.978
I was on the roof,
tagging up a billboard.

22:07.978 --> 22:10.720
I heard this loud lady
on the phone,

22:10.720 --> 22:13.070
so I looked down to see
what was going on,

22:13.070 --> 22:16.247
and car comes out of nowhere
and... [ Exhales deeply ]

22:16.247 --> 22:18.424
Jacked her up good.

22:18.424 --> 22:20.774
I know I should've called
the cops,

22:20.774 --> 22:23.690
but I had just scored,
and you know how it is.

22:23.690 --> 22:26.257
♪♪

22:32.655 --> 22:35.658
♪♪

22:40.054 --> 22:42.317
[ Door opens ]

22:42.317 --> 22:43.666
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:43.666 --> 22:45.799
[ Exhales slowly ]

22:45.799 --> 22:47.801
So...

22:47.801 --> 22:50.978
your boy Otto gave you up
real quick.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.849
Gave me up for what?

22:52.849 --> 22:57.201
You shorted Sourdough Sub stock
and had Normandy killed, right?

22:57.201 --> 23:00.335
This is how cops treat people
who come in voluntarily?

23:00.335 --> 23:05.166
Only the ones that, uh, benefit
from Normandy Parker's death.

23:05.166 --> 23:08.343
If you wanna ask me
about Normandy's finances,

23:08.343 --> 23:10.040
I'm happy to answer
any questions.

23:10.040 --> 23:11.433
But this line of questioning

23:11.433 --> 23:13.130
I'm -- I'm not very
comfortable with.

23:13.130 --> 23:15.306
Well, we have
Otto's bank records here.

23:15.306 --> 23:18.353
Money going from his account
into yours.

23:18.353 --> 23:21.574
It's only matter of time
before we connect you to Billy.

23:21.574 --> 23:25.665
Why would I hire Billy to kill
Normandy for $2 million,

23:25.665 --> 23:27.144
when I can wait for Sam

23:27.144 --> 23:28.755
to run his company
into the ground for 20?

23:32.280 --> 23:33.760
[ Chuckles ]
Shit.

23:33.760 --> 23:35.588
Ooh.

23:35.588 --> 23:39.026
Don't stop. Keep talking.

23:39.026 --> 23:42.421
Or take your chances with a jury
of your peers. Your choice.

23:44.118 --> 23:47.295
[ Sighs ] Uh...

23:47.295 --> 23:52.431
um, a few months
before Normandy was shot,

23:52.431 --> 23:56.696
Sam asked me
to transfer $4 million

23:56.696 --> 23:58.349
from Normandy's 401[k]

23:58.349 --> 24:02.049
into Sourdough Sub's
main account.

24:02.049 --> 24:04.791
He blamed it on the company
needing an influx of cash flow

24:04.791 --> 24:07.010
for their East Coast
expansion.

24:07.010 --> 24:09.578
But I-I knew that he was
full of shit.

24:09.578 --> 24:10.927
So did you do it?

24:13.887 --> 24:16.803
I would never do that
to Normandy.

24:16.803 --> 24:18.631
We were friends.

24:18.631 --> 24:21.329
So you shorted his stock
instead.

24:21.329 --> 24:23.418
That's very friendly of you.

24:23.418 --> 24:27.422
I took advantage
of a situation.

24:27.422 --> 24:29.642
Sam's been siphoning off funds
for years.

24:29.642 --> 24:32.427
I've seen his books.
They're -- they're fully cooked.Hmm.

24:32.427 --> 24:35.952
It was only a matter of time
before the stock went to zero.

24:35.952 --> 24:40.261
Robbing Peter to pay Paul
is a flawed business plan.

24:40.261 --> 24:42.916
So who's Paul in this scheme?

24:42.916 --> 24:45.962
[ Sighs ] I-I don't know.

24:45.962 --> 24:49.226
But whoever it is,
Sam owes them a lot of money.

24:49.226 --> 24:52.969
So Sam Rydell's
the next Bernie Madoff?

24:52.969 --> 24:54.928
I don't really care.

24:54.928 --> 24:58.235
You still haven't told us why
he wanted Normandy killed.

24:58.235 --> 25:00.847
How 'bout
10 million reasons?

25:00.847 --> 25:02.805
Give us one.

25:02.805 --> 25:04.590
Have either one of you
ever heard of

25:04.590 --> 25:07.070
a key man insurance policy?

25:07.070 --> 25:09.595
Sam Rydell had a $10 million
insurance policy

25:09.595 --> 25:12.206
out on Normandy Parker.

25:12.206 --> 25:13.468
Well, how do you purchase
life insurance on someone

25:13.468 --> 25:15.862
if you aren't related?[ Scoffs ]

25:15.862 --> 25:18.604
You become CEO of
a publicly traded company,

25:18.604 --> 25:20.736
and then you take out
a key man policy

25:20.736 --> 25:22.564
on that company's spokesman.

25:22.564 --> 25:25.001
Sam needed quick cash or his
whole scheme would fall apart.

25:25.001 --> 25:26.742
So his own play was to
take out Normandy

25:26.742 --> 25:28.439
and collect on the claim.

25:28.439 --> 25:30.180
So if Sam hollowed out
the company,

25:30.180 --> 25:32.618
then Normandy's stock
is virtually worthless, right?

25:32.618 --> 25:34.576
So that's why Normandy
kept playing football

25:34.576 --> 25:36.491
with that aneurysm.
He had to make the money.

25:36.491 --> 25:38.537
That means Normandy knew
what Sam was doing.

25:38.537 --> 25:41.148
No, no, no. Just another athlete
screwed over by the people

25:41.148 --> 25:43.367
he trusted the most.
Add him to the list, right?

25:43.367 --> 25:45.369
Koto: All right,
bring Sam in.

25:45.369 --> 25:46.849
Uh, all we've got are

25:46.849 --> 25:49.330
implications of financial
impropriety, right?

25:49.330 --> 25:51.375
He's the strongest lead we got.

25:51.375 --> 25:54.248
The S.C.C. and FBI will take
care of any fraud.

25:54.248 --> 25:56.990
We have two dead bodies.
Bring his ass in.

25:56.990 --> 25:59.949
Mm-hmm. All right.

25:59.949 --> 26:05.085
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

26:05.085 --> 26:07.174
Hello? [ Clears throat ]

26:08.610 --> 26:10.525
Amanda.

26:10.525 --> 26:13.354
No, calm down.

26:13.354 --> 26:15.225
Where are you right now?

26:16.836 --> 26:18.664
All right, we're on our way.

26:18.664 --> 26:22.232
♪♪

26:28.935 --> 26:31.198
Safe's empty.

26:31.198 --> 26:33.113
Oh, my God. They knew where
he kept his money.

26:33.113 --> 26:34.636
Who's they?

26:34.636 --> 26:37.552
They made him open the safe.
Don't you get it?

26:37.552 --> 26:39.293
Who are you talking about?

26:39.293 --> 26:41.687
Some Chinese guys
that came over last week.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.079
They were yelling at Sam,

26:43.079 --> 26:45.429
telling him they were gonna
break his arm

26:45.429 --> 26:47.301
if he didn't come up
with their money.

26:47.301 --> 26:48.998
Sam's a wealthy guy.

26:48.998 --> 26:50.696
What's he doing borrowing money
from Chinese thugs?

26:50.696 --> 26:54.221
He gambles, and it's not like
normal people do.

26:54.221 --> 26:57.485
He doesn't stop. The last time
he took me to Vegas,

26:57.485 --> 26:59.792
we didn't even make it
out of the casino.

26:59.792 --> 27:01.532
He just sat there
at the card table

27:01.532 --> 27:03.970
just giving them his money.

27:03.970 --> 27:06.233
All right, you came here today
to have lunch with Sam.

27:06.233 --> 27:08.061
Then what happened?

27:08.061 --> 27:10.454
I walked into the den
and I saw all of this.

27:10.454 --> 27:11.934
I figured we've been robbed.

27:11.934 --> 27:13.501
Is anything else missing?

27:13.501 --> 27:17.244
His car. I-I know that
they took him. I know they did.

27:17.244 --> 27:20.421
Ma'am, just -- just try
to calm down.You're not listening to me.

27:20.421 --> 27:21.901
His phone is still here.

27:21.901 --> 27:24.294
He doesn't go anywhere
without his phone.

27:24.294 --> 27:25.731
You can check for yourself.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.558
Okay, okay.

27:27.558 --> 27:29.038
I got it.

27:33.956 --> 27:35.915
Hildy?

27:35.915 --> 27:38.265
You might want to come
over here for a second.

27:38.265 --> 27:40.136
What is it?Nothing, ma'am.

27:46.273 --> 27:48.057
Is that blood?

27:48.057 --> 27:52.235
Oh, my God. He's dead.
They took him. I know they did.

27:52.235 --> 27:55.630
♪♪

27:55.630 --> 27:58.677
[ Utensils clinking ]

28:03.769 --> 28:05.161
This is weird.

28:05.161 --> 28:07.033
Oh.
We're out of practice.

28:07.033 --> 28:08.948
Don't worry, we'll be back to
arguing whether we should have

28:08.948 --> 28:10.689
pork chops or lemon chicken
for dinner in no time.

28:10.689 --> 28:13.082
[ Chuckles ] Well said.

28:15.084 --> 28:17.130
Can't believe what's going on
with the Normandy case.

28:17.130 --> 28:19.175
Uh, Michael.

28:19.175 --> 28:21.308
It's all anyone at school's
talking about.

28:21.308 --> 28:23.223
Well, do you think your father
wants to talk about a case

28:23.223 --> 28:26.008
that he would've had --I don't mind.

28:26.008 --> 28:28.663
I don't mind.Okay.

28:28.663 --> 28:31.753
It's the lead story
on ESPN every night.

28:31.753 --> 28:33.102
They have on
these legal experts

28:33.102 --> 28:35.191
who don't know what
they're talking about,

28:35.191 --> 28:37.063
breaking down every detail
of the case.

28:37.063 --> 28:40.719
Well, if I were still D.A.,
I would've charged Billy James.

28:40.719 --> 28:43.634
He'd still be alive
and we'd get some answers.

28:43.634 --> 28:46.899
The team is gonna wear patches
on their jerseys

28:46.899 --> 28:48.248
to honor Normandy.

28:48.248 --> 28:50.946
Number 8.
Gone, but not forgotten.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.470
I find the whole thing so sad.

28:56.125 --> 28:58.824
The roast is very good.
It's moist.[ Laughs ]

28:58.824 --> 29:00.608
Thank you.

29:00.608 --> 29:03.045
You should've seen the three
burnt ones I threw in the trash.

29:03.045 --> 29:05.656
I'm getting better.

29:05.656 --> 29:09.269
This is nice,
being all together like this.

29:09.269 --> 29:13.752
♪♪

29:18.060 --> 29:21.368
♪♪

29:26.503 --> 29:28.201
Thank you.Mm-hmm.

29:32.466 --> 29:33.815
[ Sighs ][ Dishes clatter ]

29:33.815 --> 29:35.469
You know what?

29:35.469 --> 29:37.906
You did the right thing,
convincing your mom to come.

29:37.906 --> 29:40.126
It's best for everyone.

29:40.126 --> 29:42.955
You don't know
what's best for me.

29:46.785 --> 29:50.701
I look great in red.

29:50.701 --> 29:52.486
So...

29:52.486 --> 29:54.880
Where you going?

29:54.880 --> 29:56.969
Out.

30:00.537 --> 30:04.150
[ Door closes ]Huh.

30:04.150 --> 30:07.022
[ Magazine thuds ]

30:13.812 --> 30:16.553
So I'm gone for a couple of
weeks, and you go all New Age.

30:16.553 --> 30:18.947
Yeah. It's supposed
to empower me.

30:18.947 --> 30:21.210
Mm. To do what?

30:21.210 --> 30:23.691
Take control my future.

30:23.691 --> 30:26.346
Hmm.

30:28.217 --> 30:29.784
I'm glad you came tonight.

30:29.784 --> 30:32.700
It's important that we take
this thing on together

30:32.700 --> 30:35.572
as a united front.

30:35.572 --> 30:39.750
I know about the conversation
that you had with Michael,

30:39.750 --> 30:41.274
the deal you made.

30:41.274 --> 30:42.971
He wasn't supposed
to tell you.

30:42.971 --> 30:45.452
Well, he's half you,
half me.

30:45.452 --> 30:48.281
And the good half
couldn't lie to his mother.

30:48.281 --> 30:51.327
I didn't mean to trick you
into any kind of --I know you didn't.

30:54.156 --> 30:57.507
You know,
this thing goes bad, Cass,

30:57.507 --> 31:00.380
there's no coming back.

31:00.380 --> 31:01.860
For either of us.

31:03.818 --> 31:08.257
I get how serious this is
and that's why I'm back.

31:08.257 --> 31:11.217
'Cause you need me now,
and I will be there for you.

31:11.217 --> 31:12.609
Thank you.

31:12.609 --> 31:16.613
But...I have conditions.

31:16.613 --> 31:18.572
Conditions?

31:18.572 --> 31:20.879
Actually,
more like stipulations.

31:20.879 --> 31:23.011
What, are we negotiating now?[ Chuckles ] No.

31:23.011 --> 31:26.362
This is
a take it or leave it deal.

31:26.362 --> 31:28.321
Okay.

31:28.321 --> 31:29.975
I'm listening.

31:34.153 --> 31:36.895
I need you to be 100%
honest with me from now on.

31:36.895 --> 31:39.506
No more half-truths.

31:39.506 --> 31:41.551
Never again.

31:43.640 --> 31:46.905
And I want you to treat me
as an equal,

31:46.905 --> 31:48.950
as a full partner.

31:51.561 --> 31:54.564
I promise.

31:54.564 --> 31:57.611
I'm the only one.

31:57.611 --> 32:01.441
I cannot do this
if I'm one of many.

32:01.441 --> 32:03.138
You above any.

32:10.450 --> 32:13.322
Beg for it.

32:13.322 --> 32:14.802
What?

32:16.586 --> 32:19.415
I want you

32:19.415 --> 32:21.374
to beg me for it.

32:23.071 --> 32:25.465
[ Chuckles ]

32:25.465 --> 32:28.250
I'll do whatever you want,
Cass.

32:28.250 --> 32:29.773
You know that.

32:32.646 --> 32:35.344
You know, I think I like you
like this.

32:35.344 --> 32:36.824
Oh? Like what?

32:36.824 --> 32:39.696
[ Whispers ] Mine.

32:48.618 --> 32:50.359
[ Moans ]

32:56.191 --> 32:58.237
Oh, don't even think
about it.

32:58.237 --> 33:01.196
It's not fair. All my friends
at school wear makeup.

33:01.196 --> 33:03.546
You're 11.Almost 12.

33:03.546 --> 33:07.333
Well, when you're almost 16,
we can talk about it, okay?

33:07.333 --> 33:09.335
It's not right.
The braids are too loose.

33:09.335 --> 33:11.685
Honey, I don't have time
right now.But you promised.

33:11.685 --> 33:13.730
Okay, come here.
Quick, quick, quick.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.647
Who are you going out
with tonight?

33:17.647 --> 33:19.084
Oh, just a friend.

33:19.084 --> 33:20.476
Terry?No.

33:20.476 --> 33:23.784
Then who?You -- you don't know him.

33:23.784 --> 33:25.655
Hey, stay still
or I can't do it.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.092
Another cop?

33:27.092 --> 33:28.876
No, he's -- he's not a cop.

33:28.876 --> 33:31.618
I thought you only
worked with cops.I do.

33:31.618 --> 33:33.489
I don't understand.

33:33.489 --> 33:36.275
He helps us solve crimes.How?

33:36.275 --> 33:37.972
What is with
all the questions?

33:37.972 --> 33:40.322
Just tell me what he does
and I'll leave you alone.

33:40.322 --> 33:43.064
All right, fine.

33:43.064 --> 33:45.545
He cuts up dead bodies.

33:45.545 --> 33:47.416
Gross.

33:47.416 --> 33:50.593
[ Doorbell rings ]Coming!

33:50.593 --> 33:52.030
[ Door creaks ]

33:52.030 --> 33:53.640
Hi.
Hi.

33:53.640 --> 33:55.816
Come on in.Thanks. Hello.

33:55.816 --> 33:58.079
I heard you cut up
dead bodies.

33:58.079 --> 33:59.733
[ Laughter ]

33:59.733 --> 34:03.041
[ Door closes ]You must be Louise, huh?

34:03.041 --> 34:06.435
Do they ever come back to life
like those zombies on TV?

34:06.435 --> 34:07.828
Never. Not once yet.
I've been waiting for that.

34:07.828 --> 34:09.830
And when one does,
I'm gonna call you, okay?

34:09.830 --> 34:11.571
[ Chuckles ]Okay.

34:11.571 --> 34:14.095
You look nice.Oh, thanks. So do you.

34:14.095 --> 34:16.793
Thanks. You ride?

34:16.793 --> 34:19.361
Oh. No, not since I was
a teenager. [ Chuckles ]

34:19.361 --> 34:24.975
Don't be such a wimp, Mom.Oh.

34:27.891 --> 34:29.284
Cool bike.

34:29.284 --> 34:30.807
Thank you.

34:30.807 --> 34:33.375
Um, are you cool if we just
take separate rides?

34:33.375 --> 34:35.986
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, of course.Okay.

34:35.986 --> 34:38.772
She'd love a ride
on your motorcycle.

34:38.772 --> 34:42.123
All right, fine.
Two against one. You win.

34:42.123 --> 34:45.431
I'll do it, okay?
Don't get any ideas, Louise.

34:45.431 --> 34:48.521
You're not getting on a bike
until you're 30. All right?

34:48.521 --> 34:49.913
Ready?Yeah.

34:49.913 --> 34:51.524
Bye.Good to meet you.

34:51.524 --> 34:53.656
Nice to meet you, too.Love you.

34:58.313 --> 35:00.533
You good?Yeah, I'm good.

35:00.533 --> 35:02.230
Arm.Oh, thanks.

35:02.230 --> 35:04.711
I don't wanna wipe out.
[ Chuckles ]

35:04.711 --> 35:06.800
You look nice.Oh. Well, thank you.

35:06.800 --> 35:08.323
You already said that,
but...

35:08.323 --> 35:11.152
It's worth saying it twice.[ Chuckles ]

35:11.152 --> 35:13.067
Okay.

35:13.067 --> 35:15.069
This one is yours.

35:16.940 --> 35:19.595
You ready?I guess so.

35:19.595 --> 35:23.121
All right, if I go too fast
for you, you just let me know.

35:23.121 --> 35:25.035
All right.[ Chuckles ]

35:25.035 --> 35:28.256
[ Vibrolux's "Neon Blues"
playing ]

35:30.171 --> 35:31.477
♪ You got something to explain ♪

35:31.477 --> 35:34.132
[ Engine starts ]

35:34.132 --> 35:35.742
All right, you good?

35:35.742 --> 35:37.004
Hildy: I'm good.

35:37.004 --> 35:41.269
[ Engine revving ]

35:41.269 --> 35:44.881
♪♪

35:49.190 --> 35:55.805
♪♪

35:55.805 --> 35:57.720
Nope, my dad taught me
how to ride.

35:57.720 --> 35:59.287
When I was a little kid,

35:59.287 --> 36:01.376
we used to build bikes together
in the garage

36:01.376 --> 36:03.117
and then strip 'em down and...

36:03.117 --> 36:05.554
That was actually
my introduction

36:05.554 --> 36:07.774
to doing autopsies.

36:07.774 --> 36:11.821
Hmm. Well, you ride pretty
good...for a doctor, that is.

36:11.821 --> 36:13.301
For a doctor?
Yeah.

36:13.301 --> 36:14.737
Come on.
I ride pretty good period.

36:14.737 --> 36:18.132
[ Chuckles ] You do.Thanks.

36:18.132 --> 36:19.699
A bunch of my, uh,
buddies and I,

36:19.699 --> 36:21.570
we go up to Sturgis
every year, you know?

36:21.570 --> 36:24.007
What's Sturgis?
[ Sniffs ]

36:24.007 --> 36:25.661
You don't know Sturgis?No.

36:25.661 --> 36:28.055
Okay, so it's a town
in South Dakota,

36:28.055 --> 36:29.796
but every year in August,

36:29.796 --> 36:32.190
they have the biggest
motorcycle rally in the nation.

36:32.190 --> 36:35.280
But it's a 1,400-mile ride
from here.

36:35.280 --> 36:37.064
Okay.

36:37.064 --> 36:40.807
Hildy, you've not lived
until you've ridden 1,400 miles

36:40.807 --> 36:43.157
on the open road on a bike.

36:43.157 --> 36:45.072
Really?
Yep.

36:45.072 --> 36:47.944
You're a total motorhead.

36:47.944 --> 36:49.294
Let's just say there's
a little more to me

36:49.294 --> 36:51.557
than just cutting up
dead bodies.

36:51.557 --> 36:52.993
No, I like it.

36:52.993 --> 36:55.561
Well, my ex did not,
but thank you.

36:55.561 --> 36:57.737
Mm.

36:57.737 --> 37:00.479
I'm sorry that you guys
couldn't work things out.

37:00.479 --> 37:03.830
I wasn't supposed
to bring that up.Why?

37:03.830 --> 37:06.180
You're not supposed to bring up
ex-relationships

37:06.180 --> 37:09.401
on a first date.
That is rule number one.

37:09.401 --> 37:11.838
According to who?

37:11.838 --> 37:14.797
According to an article
I read in "Cosmo."

37:14.797 --> 37:16.538
"Cosmo"?

37:16.538 --> 37:17.931
Mm-hmm.
[ Laughs ]

37:17.931 --> 37:19.280
Don't go dissing
on "Cosmo."

37:19.280 --> 37:20.934
It's a valuable source
of information

37:20.934 --> 37:22.240
for the recently divorced

37:22.240 --> 37:23.806
who would like to ignite
a second act.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.330
So...

37:25.330 --> 37:28.942
Is that what this is?
A second act?

37:31.118 --> 37:34.469
Well...I'm hoping.

37:34.469 --> 37:37.951
Cheers.[ Glass clinks ]

37:37.951 --> 37:41.215
Man: Sourdough Sub stock is down
15% in after hours trading

37:41.215 --> 37:43.043
off reports that SFPD
is searching

37:43.043 --> 37:45.480
for missing CEO
and founder Sam Rydell.

37:45.480 --> 37:48.614
Hey, I just wanted to
give you an update on Sam.

37:48.614 --> 37:50.442
Yeah, gone missing. I heard.

37:50.442 --> 37:53.749
Right.
Well, we will find him.

37:53.749 --> 37:55.577
We'll find him, sir.

37:55.577 --> 37:58.145
Uh, if you don't need anything
else, I was gonna head home.

37:58.145 --> 38:01.191
You know, every time we make
progress in this case,

38:01.191 --> 38:03.324
we hit a dead end.

38:03.324 --> 38:05.848
Sam will pop up, sir.

38:05.848 --> 38:10.026
It's really difficult
these days to, uh, disappear.

38:10.026 --> 38:12.551
Soon as he breathes,
we'll get him.

38:12.551 --> 38:14.074
Sit.

38:19.035 --> 38:21.603
I won't tell if you don't.Uh-oh!

38:24.345 --> 38:25.825
[ Snips ]

38:28.915 --> 38:30.395
[ Snips ]

38:30.395 --> 38:32.745
So, uh, word has it that
you're going out

38:32.745 --> 38:35.182
for the, uh, the D.A. job.

38:35.182 --> 38:37.663
Is that true?

38:37.663 --> 38:40.405
Nah.

38:40.405 --> 38:42.276
That's just a rumor.

38:42.276 --> 38:44.539
There you go.

38:44.539 --> 38:46.367
[ Clears throat ]

38:46.367 --> 38:49.675
No, I probably shouldn't
tell you this, but...

38:49.675 --> 38:51.807
I got offered something
last year.

38:51.807 --> 38:55.420
Mnh-mnh.I turned it down.

38:55.420 --> 38:59.119
For real? Why?

38:59.119 --> 39:00.860
Mm.

39:00.860 --> 39:02.296
[ Lighter clicks ]

39:02.296 --> 39:03.776
[ Exhales ]

39:03.776 --> 39:06.866
Come on, leave this place
to go practice law?

39:06.866 --> 39:09.216
[ Case closes ]I couldn't do it.

39:12.785 --> 39:14.743
Hey, man.

39:14.743 --> 39:17.093
I know you've been through
the ringer recently.

39:17.093 --> 39:18.834
But you'll get past this.

39:18.834 --> 39:21.141
All right, you'll feel
like a cop again.

39:21.141 --> 39:24.274
[ Sighs ] Man, I hope so.

39:24.274 --> 39:27.626
There's baggage that comes
with the job.

39:27.626 --> 39:32.152
Sometimes it's personal,
sometimes it's professional.

39:32.152 --> 39:35.895
Most of the time, it's both.

39:35.895 --> 39:38.767
But it's worth it.

39:38.767 --> 39:41.379
Only people who wear the badge
know that.

39:41.379 --> 39:43.250
You know, you can't explain it
to someone.

39:43.250 --> 39:46.862
You can't -- you can't tell them
what it's like to be a cop.

39:52.651 --> 39:56.568
So, uh, how's Hildy doing
with all this, huh?

39:56.568 --> 39:58.613
She -- she hate me now?
[ Laughs ]

39:58.613 --> 40:03.226
[ Telephone rings ]

40:03.226 --> 40:05.403
[ Ring ]

40:08.057 --> 40:09.624
Koto.

40:11.147 --> 40:13.454
Where?

40:13.454 --> 40:14.934
Yeah, we're on our way.[ Hangs up receiver ]

40:14.934 --> 40:18.328
Put those out.
We're on the move.

40:19.895 --> 40:21.810
Okay, what do we got?

40:21.810 --> 40:23.464
Vehicle registration,
Detective.

40:23.464 --> 40:25.423
[ Engine rumbling ]

40:26.946 --> 40:29.862
[ Rumbling continues ]

40:29.862 --> 40:31.603
Oh, boy.

40:34.083 --> 40:36.042
[ Sighs ]

40:36.042 --> 40:37.347
Thanks.

40:37.347 --> 40:40.002
All right, see ya.Yeah.

40:40.002 --> 40:42.527
[ Engine revving ]

40:42.527 --> 40:45.138
[ Exhales deeply ] Hey.

40:45.138 --> 40:48.054
Hey.
Sam's car?

40:48.054 --> 40:50.491
Yeah. [ Clears throat ]

40:50.491 --> 40:52.972
No damage.

40:52.972 --> 40:55.278
Clearly, he wasn't forced
off the road.

40:55.278 --> 40:58.847
Whoever he was with
had his keys.

40:58.847 --> 41:00.849
See if there's
anything inside.

41:02.677 --> 41:05.201
I got something here.
It's a jacket.

41:07.465 --> 41:09.467
What's this?

41:09.467 --> 41:11.469
S.R.Sam Rydell.

41:13.079 --> 41:15.211
Uh-huh.

41:17.475 --> 41:20.521
Wang Fun Karaoke Bar. Huh.

41:20.521 --> 41:23.829
Yeah, the Tongs own
that spot.

41:23.829 --> 41:26.353
So he owed the Tongs money,
couldn't pay up,

41:26.353 --> 41:28.921
they threw him off the bridge.

41:28.921 --> 41:32.838
Or they tried to scare him
and something happened.

41:34.796 --> 41:39.497
Either way,
it's a long way down.

41:43.762 --> 41:46.765
♪♪
